premise_source_doc_sentence: The Ensuring Lawful Collection of Hidden Assets to Provide Order Act  (  H.R. 2186  )  , abbreviated as the EL CHAPO Act , is a United States Congress bill that would reserve any amount of money seized by the U.S. Government as a result of the criminal prosecution of Joaquín `` El Chapo '' Guzmán and other felony convictions involving the transportation of controlled substances into the United States for security measures along the U.S.-Mexico border and the construction of a border wall .
